Dryocosmus hualieni

: the bottom of scutellar foveae with numerous longitudinal rugae (Fig. 
83
); female F1 / F2<1; the female F1 / pedicel = 1.6; placoid sensilla are present on F2-F12 (Fig. 
81
); the frons is alutaceous; the acetabular sulcus absent, the speculum is without striae (Fig. 
84
), the mesoscutellum rounded, anterior part without rugae, glabrous (Fig. 
83
).

Dryocosmus taitungensis

: the frons is coriaceous, with numerous transverse striae above toruli; the acetabular carina present; the speculum with striae (Fig. 
166
); the mesoscutellum trapezoid, uniformly rugose, matt (Fig. 
167
).
